Azure Project: Manage Azure Active Directory (Microsoft Entra ID) Identities
Project Level

Novice (Beginner-friendly, Azure Portal only)

This project is designed as an entry-level, step-by-step Azure Portal lab focused on identity management fundamentals using Microsoft Entra ID (formerly Azure Active Directory). It assumes no prior Azure administration experience.

Project Objective

Demonstrate the ability to:

Create and manage an Azure AD (Entra ID) tenant

Create and configure Azure AD users

Create Azure AD groups with assigned and dynamic membership

Invite and manage guest (B2B) users

This project reflects real-world tasks performed by Cloud Support and Junior Systems Administrators.

Skills Demonstrated

Identity and Access Management (IAM)

Microsoft Entra ID administration

Azure Portal navigation

User and group lifecycle management

Basic governance and security concepts

Environment & Tools

Azure Portal

Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD)

Azure Free Tier Subscription

Architecture Overview (Logical)

Azure Subscription

Entra ID Tenant

Internal Users

Security Groups (Assigned & Dynamic)

External Guest User

Step-by-Step Deployment & Configuration
Step 1: Verify or Create an Entra ID Tenant

Objective: Ensure an Entra ID tenant exists for identity management.

Steps:

Sign in to the Azure Portal

Search for Microsoft Entra ID

Review the Overview page to confirm a tenant exists

Optional (Create New Tenant):

Microsoft Entra ID â†’ Manage tenants â†’ Create

Tenant type: Microsoft Entra ID

Provide:

Organization name

Initial domain name

Region

Review + Create

Expected Outcome:

Entra ID tenant is active and accessible

